cyclone.name: NESTOR
cyclone.current_location: about 85 miles SW of Apalachicola, Florida
cyclone.trajectory: continuing northeast toward the Florida Panhandle, then forecast to track across the southeastern United States and move offshore of North Carolina into the western Atlantic

weather_observation.watch_coast: None for Texas coastline; existing watch applies only Navarre FL to Yankeetown FL
weather_observation.warning_coast: Tropical Storm Warning from Navarre Florida to Yankeetown Florida (Florida Gulf Coast)
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Primary impacts limited to Florida Gulf Coast, then portions of GA/SC/NC coasts as the system moves inland and offshore
weather_observation.closest_wind_data_location: None (no wind-probability point reported near south Texas)
